t Asian American mental health—and vice versa. Interspersed throughout the book are reflective activities, including original tarot cards, that enact the very pedagogy Khúc advances, offering readers alternative ways of being that divest from structures of unwellness and open new possibilities for collective care.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aAsian American studentsxMental health. 0aAsian AmericansxMental health. 0aAsian AmericansxPsychology. 0aAsian AmericansxSocial conditions. 0aCOVID-19 Pandemic, 2020-zUnited States. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Ethnic Studies / Asian American Studies.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDuke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2024z978311135689140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781478027799?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478027799423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781478027799/original  a978-3-11-135689-1  Duke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2024b2024  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles